public class NewClass {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		AA a1 = new AA();
		System.out.println("Memory of a1 : "+a1);
		BB b1 = new BB();
		System.out.println("Memory of b1 : "+b1);
		String s = b1.toString();
		System.out.println("s = "+s);
		
	}
}
class AA
{
	String a;
}
class BB
{
	String b;
	public String toString()
	{
		return "Class is BB";
	}
}

Output:
Memory of a1 : classtest.AA@34a245ab
Memory of b1 : Class is BB
s = Class is BB

Initially, the value of a class is its memory address.But, by toString() method we can assign value to the class as our wish.
